Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Progeny \Prog"e*ny\, n. [OE. progenie, F. prog['e]nie, fr. L. progenies, fr. progignere. See {Progenitor}.] Descendants of the human kind, or offspring of other animals; children; offspring; race, lineage. `` Issued from the progeny of kings.'' --Shak. [1913 Webster]
progeny n : the immediate descendants of a person; "she was the mother of many offspring"; "he died without issue" [syn: {offspring}, {issue}]
